&lt;p&gt;Community Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Fylde Coast Older Adult Community Mental Health Team (CMHT) was formed April 2015 following a restructure of services and now covers the Geographical area of Blackpool, Fylde &amp; Wyre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Service &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours: Monday to Friday 9.00am to 5.00pm&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service will provide specialist assessment and treatment, and high quality support for older people with complex mental health and social care needs, including people with dementia. The key focus will be one of therapeutic optimism and service users will be assisted to maximise their quality of life by promoting recovery, social inclusion and living well with dementia and other significant mental health conditions. The service will also provide assessment and specialist support to carers and families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Both health and Social Services co locate their working practices in order to provide a seamless service for service users and their carer’s in line with the Care Act (2015)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We have an exciting opportunity for a Community Mental Health Nurse to join our team as a Care Coordinator.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You must have been a minimum of 2 years post qualification clinical work with service users experiencing a range of mental health problems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You must have experience of supervising staff, experienced in acting as a mentor/assessor of student staff&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You need to be able to work as part of a multidisciplinary team and have experience of assessing, planning and implementing and reviewing care needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You must be able to travel as part of this role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Kate Morgans - 01253 957350 - Kate.morgans@lscft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
